This paper proposes a new algorithm for reinforcement learning in continuous control tasks, which falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on actor-critic methods, which are commonly used in robotics and control systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of value prediction models and tree search, which are techniques commonly used in control systems and computer vision, respectively, suggesting cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as possible sub-categories as well.
